<A>__{suddenly it becomes clear how what we are seeing is possible the airplane is no longer in flight, but is dangling a few feet above the ground, suspended from the cable of the huge crane. the crewmen shove at its tail and wingtips to keep it revolving. cameron is, indeed, clinging to the wing strut, his feet held in space by the centrifugal force. but, if his hands slip, he will fall ten feet instead of to certain death.}
